dct_description_sm: This tabular data, prepared by Data You Can Use, presents the percentage of adults who report 14 or more poor mental health days within the preceeding 30 days by census tract in the city of Milwaukee, Wisconsin. The data is sourced from the Center for Disease Control PLACES 2023 Release, based on the Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System Data from 2021, and utilizes 2020 Census tracts. For more information, please visit Data You Can Use.
